title: Key questions as US arrests man accused of Lockerbie bombing
description: Three sentences from the United States Department of Justice confirmed this key development in the story of Lockerbie.

title: Orion spacecraft splashes back down to Earth after successful mission to moon
description: NASA's Orion spacecraft has successfully splashed down into the Pacific Ocean after a 25-day mission to the moon.

title: Man accused of making Lockerbie bomb now in US custody
description: The man accused of making the bomb that blew up the Pan Am 103 flight over Lockerbie in 1988 is now in US custody.

title: Putin could use peace talks 'as excuse to rearm and recruit troops'
description: Vladimir Putin could use any peace talks with Ukraine as an excuse to rearm and recruit Russian troops, the foreign secretary has warned.

title: 'Stick with us': Bellingham's plea to fans as England begin journey home from World Cup
description: On a despondent morning for England players, Jude Bellingham had a final message for fans before heading to a flight out of Qatar.

title: 'I'm staying here in an aggressor state': The Ukrainian refugees living in Russia's Belgorod
description: The backrooms at the local communist party headquarters near Belgorod airport are stacked high with supplies.
